{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-publication-index-js","path":"/dp/048/the-impacts-of-the-billing-system-on-healthcare-utilization-the-case-of-thai-civil-servant-medical-benefit-scheme/","result":{"data":{"meta":{"siteMetadata":{"collections":[{"collection":"abridged","title":"aBRIDGEd","subtitle":"Making Research Accessible","url":"/abridged/","placeholder":null},{"collection":"thaipublica","title":"เศรษฐศาสตร์เข้า \"ท่า\"","subtitle":"Making Research Make Sense","url":"/thaipublica/","placeholder":null},{"collection":"pierspectives","title":"PIERspectives","subtitle":"Making Research Comprehensible","url":"/pierspectives/","placeholder":"pierspectives"},{"collection":"dp","title":"Discussion Paper","subtitle":"Making Research Inaccessible","url":"/dp/","placeholder":"dp"},{"collection":"members","title":"Members","subtitle":"Making Research Possible","url":"/pier-research-network/","placeholder":null},{"collection":"announcements","title":"Announcements","subtitle":"Making Research Public","url":"/announcements/","placeholder":"announcements"},{"collection":"blog","title":"PIER Blog","subtitle":"Making Research Public","url":"/blog/","placeholder":"blog"},{"collection":"conferences","title":"Conferences","subtitle":"Making Research Big","url":"/conferences/","placeholder":"conferences"},{"collection":"workshops","title":"Workshops and Forums","subtitle":"Making Research Work","url":"/workshops/","placeholder":"seminars"},{"collection":"seminars","title":"PIER Economic Seminars","subtitle":"Making Research Better","url":"/seminars/","placeholder":"seminars"},{"collection":"exchange","title":"PIER Research Exchange","subtitle":"Making Research Exchangable","url":"/exchange/","placeholder":"seminars"}],"series":[{"series":"Industry Transformation","placeholder":"industry-transformation"},{"series":"Public Economics","placeholder":"public-economics"}]}},"mdx":{"body":"var _excluded = [\"components\"];\n\nfunction _extends() { _extends = Object.assign || function (target) { for (var i = 1; i < arguments.length; i++) { var source = arguments[i]; for (var key in source) { if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(source, key)) { target[key] = source[key]; } } } return target; }; return _extends.apply(this, arguments); }\n\nfunction _objectWithoutProperties(source, excluded) { if (source == null) return {}; var target = _objectWithoutPropertiesLoose(source, excluded); var key, i; if (Object.getOwnPropertySymbols) { var sourceSymbolKeys = Object.getOwnPropertySymbols(source); for (i = 0; i < sourceSymbolKeys.length; i++) { key = sourceSymbolKeys[i]; if (excluded.indexOf(key) >= 0) continue; if (!Object.prototype.propertyIsEnumerable.call(source, key)) continue; target[key] = source[key]; } } return target; }\n\nfunction _objectWithoutPropertiesLoose(source, excluded) { if (source == null) return {}; var target = {}; var sourceKeys = Object.keys(source); var key, i; for (i = 0; i < sourceKeys.length; i++) { key = sourceKeys[i]; if (excluded.indexOf(key) >= 0) continue; target[key] = source[key]; } return target; }\n\n/* @jsxRuntime classic */\n\n/* @jsx mdx */\nvar _frontmatter = {\n  \"id\": \"048\",\n  \"title\": \"The Impacts of the Billing System on Healthcare Utilization: The Case of Thai Civil Servant Medical Benefit Scheme\",\n  \"authors\": [\"Nada Wasi\", \"Jirawat Panpiemras\", \"Wanwiphang Manachotphong\"],\n  \"date\": \"2016-11-16T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"pdf\": \"pier_dp_048.pdf\"\n};\nvar layoutProps = {\n  _frontmatter: _frontmatter\n};\nvar MDXLayout = \"wrapper\";\nreturn function MDXContent(_ref) {\n  var components = _ref.components,\n      props = _objectWithoutProperties(_ref, _excluded);\n\n  return mdx(MDXLayout, _extends({}, layoutProps, props, {\n    components: components,\n    mdxType: \"MDXLayout\"\n  }), mdx(\"p\", null, \"While a large number of health insurance studies find that an increase in cost-sharing reduces healthcare demand, little has looked at the effect of a policy change operating through a non-price channel. This paper examines how a billing process can affect healthcare utilization given no change in price. Specifically, we look at the launch of the Direct Billing Payment program (DBP) to the Thai Civil Servant Medical Benefit Scheme. In the past, although the outpatient care is essentially free, its beneficiaries must pay at the point of services and get their money reimbursed later. The DBP allows the hospitals to charge the government directly. Using patient-level panel data from a large regional hospital, we find that the new billing system affects utilization through multiple channels. First, it increases the number of outpatient visits. Second, for each visit, the treatment costs and the share of prescription drug charge are higher. These impacts are found to be persistent over time, although less so in the case of visits. In addition, our analysis suggests that the likely cash constrained patients increase their utilization more proportionally.\"));\n}\n;\nMDXContent.isMDXComponent = true;","fields":{"slug":"/dp/048/the-impacts-of-the-billing-system-on-healthcare-utilization-the-case-of-thai-civil-servant-medical-benefit-scheme/","collection":"dp","shorturl":"/dp/048/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"The Impacts of the Billing System on Healthcare Utilization: The Case of Thai Civil Servant Medical Benefit Scheme","subtitle":null,"series":null,"authors":["Nada Wasi","Jirawat Panpiemras","Wanwiphang Manachotphong"],"date":"2016-11-16T00:00:00.000Z","updated":null,"cover":null,"excerpt":null,"bibliography":null,"topics":null,"tags":null,"layout":null,"pdf":{"publicURL":"/static/e40c28dd73f24de1d531b7510139fca0/pier_dp_048.pdf"}},"authors":[{"frontmatter":{"memberid":"Jirawat Panpiemras","title":"Jirawat Panpiemras","org":"tdri","email":"jirawat@tdri.or.th","image":{"childImageSharp":{"gatsbyImageData":{"layout":"constrained","backgroundColor":"#b8b8b8","images":{"fallback":{"src":"/static/01029099ddddac92ad7e0782c57c8947/dd515/profile.jpg",